  "text": "The anesthetized mouse was then moved onto the stage of a dual photon microscope (LSM 510, Zeiss Inc., Germany). Medial femoral condyle cartilage was imaged using a 40×1.00 NA water-immersion objective (Zeiss Inc., Germany) coupled with a Chameleon XR infrared laser (Coherent Inc., USA). Two photon microscopy was used so that we could penetrate the entire In Vivo Deformation of Articular Cartilage during Muscular Contraction medial compartment cartilage and to reduce photo bleaching and photo damage encountered with regular confocal microscopy [CITATION_1] .",
